You can stay here at night. There is a provision for staying and sleeping here. This mosque is three storeyed in which more than five thousand people offer namaz on Jumma. There is a dense population of Muslims all around the mosque and there are shops in it. There is a lot of crowd! Thank you!!

featured_reviews.review_translated_text: The Dargah courtyard is quite open. Actually there are two dargahs here. The main dargah here is of Hazrat Ahsan Shah. There is also a pond in the Dargah complex itself. There is a belief that if anyone suffering from itching takes a bath in the pond water, the itching goes away. This is correct. Although there is no shop for flowers, incense sticks etc. in the Dargah premises, still if you want to light incense sticks, it is available. There is a lot of peace. You can pray sitting comfortably.
